The paper focuses on visual question answering (VQA) using deep representation learning for visual recognition and language understanding, as well as symbolic program execution for reasoning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency and robustness of the proposed method, which could be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
